### 19. Reactive Draft Updates

**Rule:** Subscribe to pending drafts via query, update UI automatically when status changes.

```typescript
// ✅ DO: Subscribe to drafts
const pendingDrafts = useQuery(
  api.assistant.listPendingDrafts,
  threadId ? { threadId } : 'skip'
)

// UI updates automatically when draft approved/discarded
{pendingDrafts?.map(draft => (
  draft.status === 'draft' && <DraftCard {...draft} />
))}

// ❌ DON'T: Poll or manual refresh
const [drafts, setDrafts] = useState([])
useEffect(() => {
  const interval = setInterval(async () => {
    const result = await fetchDrafts()
    setDrafts(result)
  }, 1000)
}, [])
```

**Why:** Convex reactivity handles updates automatically, no polling needed.

## Testing

### 20. Test Scope Enforcement

**Rule:** Every agent tool must have tests for scope boundary violations.

```typescript
// ✅ DO: Test cross-classroom rejection
test('AI cannot create care log outside teacher scope', async () => {
  const t = convexTest(schema)
  
  // Teacher in Sunflower Room
  const { teacherId, sunflowerId } = await setupTeacher(t, 'Sunflower Room')
  
  // Create AI thread
  const { threadId } = await t.mutation(api.assistant.createSession, {})
  
  // Child in Butterfly Room (different classroom)
